description: AntennaUnitGroup:  This table stores metadata about groups of antenna units at a specific cell, including timestamp, location, and identifiers.  `dateTime`: Timestamp of the record; `Area_Name`: Geographic area of the cell; `CellId`: Unique identifier for the cell; `Id2`: Redundant cell identifier; `Id3`:  Another identifier for the antenna unit group (possibly a sub-group); `vsDataType`: Data type identifier; `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of the data format; `AntennaUnitGroup.positionRef`: Reference to position data (currently empty); `AntennaUnitGroup.positionInformation`: Position information (currently empty); `AntennaUnitGroup.antennaUnitGroupId`: Unique identifier for the antenna unit group.
queries: Find all AntennaUnitGroups in Area_Name 'Downtown' with vsDataFormatVersion 2.0.
Show me the AntennaUnitGroup.antennaUnitGroupId for all records where Id2 is null.
What is the latest dateTime for AntennaUnitGroups with CellId 'XYZ123'?
Retrieve all AntennaUnitGroups where vsDataType is 'LTE' and Area_Name contains 'Suburb'.
Count the number of AntennaUnitGroups for each unique CellId, ordered by count descending.
